The paper focuses on developing a tool to detect related bugs in open source projects using bug information and code features. This involves extracting bug features from bug repositories, locating bug methods from source code, and calculating similarities between overridden or overloaded methods and bug methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing source code, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to calculate similarities between methods could also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
